  <h3 id="how_to_play">How to Play</h3>

  <p>Your goal is to beat as many <b>blinds</b> as possible. To pass a blind, you need to play the required <a href="#poker_hands">poker hands</a>. Sounds easy, right?</p>
  <p>For each blind, you can only play <b>3 hands</b> and <b>4 discards</b>. Every time you want to make one of those moves, you must draw a <b>question card</b>. If you answer correctly, you can perform the action. If not, the opposite happens.</p>
  <p>Each player starts with a hand of <b>8 cards</b>. After each play or discard, your hand is refilled.</p>
  <p>After each blind, the player receives <b class="yellow">3 dollars</b> to spend in the shop. There, they can buy up to <b>2 <a href="#jokers">jokers</a></b>, which can help them finish the round.</p>

